Andy Powell: Wigan Warriors new boy says time right to switch codes
Media playback is not supported on this deviceAndy Powell tells BBC North West Tonight that he believes his game will be suited to rugby league after switching codes to join Super League leaders Wigan Warriors.The 31-year-old, capped 23 times by Wales, has signed a contract until 2015 and will link up with Wigan once he has concluded the Premiership season with Sale.